article.headline: Towson 75, Delaware 74
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Rocky Coleman scored 21 points and Towson defeated Delaware 75-74 on Wednesday night. Delaware led 57-53 with 9 minutes left, but Towson (10-20, 5-12 Colonial Athletic Association) scored 10 unanswered points, including back-to-back 3-pointers by Coleman, to take a 63-57 lead with 7:30 to play. The Blue Hens (12-18, 5-12) cut the deficit to 71-70 on a 3-pointer by Brian Johnson with 2:51 to go. Towson's Junior Hairston responded with two baskets for a 75-70 advantage with 1:38 left, sealing the win. Hairston added 13 points and nine rebounds and Calvin Lee chipped in with 13 points for the Tigers, who snapped a three game losing streak. Marc Egerson paced the Blue Hens with 23 points and Johnson added 14. The first meeting between the two teams also resulted in a one-point game. Towson won 62-61 on in Newark, Del. on Jan. 5.
